"As we kick off the start of the new school year, we want to ensure that students and families have as many mental health resources as possible. In that effort, Winters JUSD has developed a Virtual Wellness Center. The Virtual Wellness Center includes resources for parents and students related to the current wildfires, COVID-19, mental health awareness, and mental health helplines. There is also a virtual calming room that includes sections like exercise, guided meditation, creative activities, and much more."

here is the website link: https://sites.google.com/wintersjusd.org/wellnesscenter/home?authuser=0

post_text:
Good Afternoon Winters Community,
We hope that you and your families are safe. Due to the fire, changing conditions, and poor air quality, we are canceling our family technology night tonight. We will be creating videos of all presentations so that all families can access the resources virtually. The videos will be available later next week, sent to families, and posted on school websites.

Buenas tardes comunidad de Winters,
Esperamos que ustedes y sus familias estén bien. Debido al incendio, las condiciones cambiantes y la mala calidad del aire, esta noche cancelaremos nuestra noche de tecnología familiar. Crearemos videos de todas las presentaciones para que todas las familias puedan tener acceso a los recursos virtualmente. Los videos estarán disponibles la próxima semana, se enviarán a las familias, y se publicarán en los sitios web de las escuelas.

Estimados padres:

WJUSD está considerando actualmente cómo reabrir las escuelas en Agosto 2020. La decisión para reabrir las escuelas tendrá en cuenta las recomendaciones del Departamento de Salud Pública del Condado de Yolo, el Centro para el Control de Enfermedades (CDC), el Estado de California y del Departamento de Educación de California. La Mesa Directiva determinara el modelo para empezar las clases.

Su opinion es muy importante. Gracias por completar esta encuesta. Este es un tiempo muy desafiante para todos. Queremos asegurar la mejor educación para todos nuestros estudiantes y también asegurar su salud y seguridad.

Gracias por ser nuestros compañeros en la educación de sus niños.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

WJUSD is currently considering how we will reopen schools in August 2020. The decision on reopening will take into account the guidance from Yolo County Public Health, the Center for Disease Control, the State of California and the California Department of Education. The Board of Trustees will make the final determination on the school reopening model.

Your input and opinion is important. Thank you for taking the time to complete this survey. This is a very challenging time for everyone. We want to ensure the best education for all of our students and also ensure their health and safety.

Thank you for being our partners in the education of your children.

https://forms.gle/f5Kg9kmhbYB89rdD7

Press Release – May 22, 2020
Winters Joint Unified School District
Notice of Governing Board Member Election

At its May 21, 2020 Board meeting the Board of Trustees unanimously approved Board Resolution No. 1122-20 – Notice of Governing Board Member Election. The November 3, 2020 election will be held to fill the vacancies for the terms specified for the following Trustee Areas:
Trustee Area #1 (2020-2024)
Trustee Area #3 (2020-2022)
Trustee Area #5 (2020-2024)
Filing dates for candidates are from July 13, 2020 through August 7, 2020. Each candidate is required to file in person at the County Elections Office located within the trustee area boundary.
For more information contact the Winters School District Office at 530-795-6100.

post_text: Joseph and Sophia Jara spent time yesterday cleaning up around Dollar General.. Joseph is in kindergarten at Waggoner and Sophia is a third grader at Rominger. What an amazing show of community!! Thanks Jara family❤️❤️
shared_text:
Jose Jara‎Winters Community Info and Tips
April 3 at 8:46 AM ·

I brought kids out today to do some community service. We cleaned up several bags full of garbage in the dollar general area. They were actually excited to help the community. We got many offers of monetary gratitude from members of the community that we turned down but appreciated the offer and this is a huge reason why we love our small town. In the end the employees working at dollar general were so appreciative and even contacted their manager to give the kids a small reward. (FYI: the kids were wearing gloves and used tools to pick up the trash, used hand sanitizer when they finished and thoroughly washed their hands when we got home)

post_text:
Update Regarding Incident at WHS on December 9th:

We would like to provide updated information from what we reported on Monday. First, I would like to compliment the High School staff for their quick response in this situation. I (Todd Cutler) was on campus at the time of the gathering of students in the Library parking lot and Principal Mr. Barsotti and I were in the area of the library within moments of the call. We were able to determine quickly that there was no threat to the school or students. Our team worked effectively with our safety partners as we addressed this issue. The Winters Police Department has informed us that there was no evidence to substantiate or verify that there was a weapon present. Thank you for your continued support and understanding.
Winters JUSD

Todd

post_text:
October 9th, 2019

Parents, Families, and Friends:

I want to thank everyone for their support and flexibility with the challenge of the loss of power. As you may know, today we had power at Winters High School and Winters Middle School, however power was out at Waggoner, Rominger, Wolfskill and Preschool.
We have been informed that we will not be losing power to sites that have maintained power and that we should expect power to return to the other sites by tomorrow afternoon. With this said, we are going to move forward with school tomorrow. We will have a regular schedule for Middle School and High School, Wolfskill, and Preschool. Rominger and Waggoner will remain on a shortened schedule (Wednesday schedule). Transportation and Food Services will be fully functional.
At this time we are planning for a regular school day for all, on Friday. We will continue to monitor the situation and send another update tomorrow.

Thanks,
Todd Cutler, Ed.D.
Superintendent
Winters Joint Unified School District

post_text:
Parents, Families, and Friends:

We were informed last night that the PG&E would most likely shut power off to our community at midnight tonight. The City has confirmed that we will have water and sewer service and our Food Service Team will be able to serve meals. With that said, we plan to have school as scheduled tomorrow Wednesday October 9th.

If power does go down, every school site will have a phone line that works; we ask that you reserve calls for emergencies only to keep those lines open. We will post updates to our Facebook Page www.facebook.com/wintersjusd/ and Website wintersjusd.org with any additional information, as well as sending messages via text.

Tomorrow we will assess the day and determine if we can remain open for Thursday and Friday.

post_text: Happy Tuesday... Please join me in welcoming our newest Teacher... Dianne Halsey is joining us as our CTE Engineering Teacher at Winters High School. Dianne comes to us with a MA in Education, a Multiple Subject Teaching credential, a CTE Engineering credential and 16 years of teaching experience. Dianne has lead her robotics clubs to 3 CA State Championships & 3 World Championships. We are very excited to have Dianne join our team here in Winters and look forward to her sharing her passion for Engineering and Robotics with our kids. Welcome to Winters Dianne!!!

On Thursday, March 21, 2019 the Winters JUSD School Board approved the appointment of Jennifer Kloczko as Waggoner Elementary Principal 2019-2020. Jennifer comes to us with 17 years of K-5 teaching experience, 6 years of administrative experience and a passion for early literacy. Jennifer holds a BA in Liberal Studies, a Multiple Subject Teaching Credential and a clear Administrative Credential.

Jennifer will begin her position as Principal – Waggoner Elementary on July 1, 2019.

post_text:
Good Friday evening, Parents & Guardians:

The Winters Joint Unified School District will be conducting a District-wide Lock-down Drill on Monday, December 3, 2018 at approximately 9:10 AM. This District-wide drill will include communication to parents. This communication will be automated and it will be clear that it is only a drill. It is important that all parents know this is happening to avoid the perception that it might be an actual emergency. You should expect three calls during this time. The first call will inform you of a lock-down. The second call will provide you with instructions if this was a real situation. The last call will inform you that we are all clear.

post_text:
Winters School Closure for Friday November 16, 2018

Good afternoon, Parents & Guardians.

After consultation with superintendents throughout Yolo County, all schools in the Winters Joint Unified School District will be closed tomorrow, Friday, November 16 due to the health concerns related to the smoke.

Under normal circumstances we would remain open at Air Quality Index levels of 151 to 200. However, we have concerns about the continued increases in AQI and prolonged exposure to staff and students occurring this week.

I wish you all a happy Thanksgiving with friends and family.
